<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n25077e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n25" href="#n25077e">N25 (VI.B.15)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n25all.htm#n25077e"> 77(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> lad who lives at 47</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Gregor says that &lsquo;in Buckie there are certain family names that fishermen will not pronounce,&rsquo; the folk in the village of Coull speaking of &lsquo;spitting out the bad name.&rsquo; If such a name be mentioned in their hearing, they spit, or, in the vernacular,&lsquo;chiff,&rsquo; and the man who bears the dreaded name is called a &lsquo;chifferoot.&rsquo; When occasion to speak of him arises, a circumlocutory phrase is used, as &lsquo;The man it diz so in so,&rsquo; or &lsquo;The <mark>laad it lives at such and such a place</mark>.&rsquo; <small> Edward Clodd, <a name="ECTTT" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#ECTTT"><cite title="source">Tom Tit Tot</cite></a> (1898) 118</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c14046a" href="c14all.htm#c14046a">VI.C.14:046(a)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
